tical and sometimes physical—against nazis, the Ku Klux Klan, anti-abortion fundamentalists, and racist police. Before media pundits, cynical politicians, and your uncle discovered “antifa,” Anti-Racist Action was bringing it to the streets.Based on extensive interviews with dozens of ARA participants, We Go Where They Go tells ARA’s story from within, giving voice to those who risked their safety in their own defense and in solidarity with others. In reproducing the posters, zines, propaganda and photos of the movement itself, this essential work of radical history illustrates how cultural scenes can become powerful forces for change. Here at last is the story of an organic yet highly organized movement, exploring both its triumphs and failures, and offering valuable lessons for today’s generation of activists and rabble-rousers. We Go Where They Go is a page-turning history of grassroots anti-racism. More than just inspiration, it's a roadmap.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Activism & Social Justice.2bisacsh  aARA.  aBlack Lives Matter.  aCanadian anti-fascist.  aCanadian anti-racist organizing.  aCanadian hate groups.  aRoe v. Wade.  aactivism.  aanarchism.  aanti-fascism.  aanti-fascist history.  aanti-fascist.  aanti-racism.  aanti-racist action.  aanti-racist history.  aantifa.  abooks about anti-racism.  afighting racism.  agrassroots organizing.  ahate crimes.  apro-choice.  aprotest.  apunk rock.  asolidarity.  atrucker convoy.1 aHill, Gord, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwartz, Kristin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStaudenmaier, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 